{"timestamp": "2025-12-04 23:01:50.904948", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\n\nExecutive summary\n- Anomaly detected: Endpoint pc_0_0 is down (container not running), causing loss of host-to-host reachability to 10.0.0.2.\n- Control-plane health: EBGP across leaves, spines, and super-spine appears fully established and stable.\n- Data-plane: Local gateway connectivity from pc_0_1 is normal; inter-host traffic to pc_0_0 fails due to the endpoint being offline, not a routing failure.\n\nFindings and evidence\n\n1) Endpoint status and basic reachability\n- pc_0_0:\n  - Network config retrieval failed with explicit container state error:\n    - “container ... is not running”\n  - This indicates the host is offline/unavailable.\n- pc_0_1:\n  - IP: 10.0.1.2/24, default via 10.0.1.1 (leaf_router_0_1).\n  - Ping to default gateway (10.0.1.1) succeeds (0% loss, sub-ms RTT).\n  - Ping to remote host 10.0.0.2 fails with “Destination Host Unreachable” sourced from 172.16.1.81.\n\nInterpretation: pc_0_1 has correct local L3 connectivity. Failure to reach 10.0.0.2 is consistent with the destination host pc_0_0 being offline. The ICMP unreachable originated from leaf_router_0_0’s fabric-facing interface (172.16.1.81), confirming the packet reached the remote leaf, which could not forward to a non-existent host.\n\n2) Router interface and ARP-facing observations\n- leaf_router_0_1 (10.0.1.1/24 to pc_0_1):\n  - eth8 shows RX/TX consistent with local pings.\n- leaf_router_0_0 (10.0.0.1/24 to pc_0_0):\n  - eth8 shows RX 0, TX 1 (no traffic received from a host), corroborating that the attached host is not active on the link.\n\n3) EBGP control-plane health\n- Leaves (leaf_router_0_0 AS 65200, leaf_router_0_1 AS 65201):\n  - “show ip bgp summary” shows all neighbors established with expected PfxRcd counts.\n- Spines (spine_router_0_0 AS 65100, spine_router_0_1 AS 65101):\n  - All EBGP sessions to super-spine and leaves are established; multiple 10.x.x.0/24 routes are present.\n- Super-spine (AS 65000):\n  - All spine sessions established; prefixes are exchanged normally.\n\n4) Routing tables (selected)\n- leaf_router_0_1:\n  - Has BGP-learned route to 10.0.0.0/24 via 172.16.1.82 (toward spine), and directly connected 10.0.1.0/24 on eth8.\n- leaf_router_0_0:\n  - Has BGP-learned route to 10.0.1.0/24 via 172.16.1.80 (toward spine), and directly connected 10.0.0.0/24 on eth8.\n- Spines:\n  - Show routes to both 10.0.0.0/24 and 10.0.1.0/24 via the appropriate leaf next-hops.\nInterpretation: The Clos EBGP control plane and inter-pod reachability are correctly programmed; routing is not the cause of the host reachability failure.\n\nLocalization of the fault\n- Faulty device: pc_0_0 (endpoint/host).\n- Evidence: Container “not running” error; no RX activity on its connected leaf interface; ICMP Unreachable returned by the remote leaf when attempting to reach 10.0.0.2.\n\nRoot cause\n- pc_0_0 is offline (container stopped/not running), making 10.0.0.2 unreachable. The network fabric is healthy; the failure is isolated to the endpoint itself.\n\nImpact\n- East-west traffic to/from 10.0.0.2 (pc_0_0) fails. Other control/data-plane functions remain normal, as evidenced by healthy BGP adjacencies and correct routing tables.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 22279, "output_tokens": 2659, "total_tokens": 24938, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 0}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 1728}}}
